.\" termin.al-name: echo
.\" termin.al-usage: echo [text ...]
.\" termin.al-summary: Print arguments as text.
.TH ECHO 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
echo \- Print arguments as text.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
echo [text ...]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Writes its parsed arguments as one line of text, separated by single spaces. Shell quoting controls argument boundaries and is not reproduced in the output.
.SH OUTPUT
With no arguments, echo emits an empty text output. Option-looking arguments are printed as ordinary text; echo implements no flags or escape expansion.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ echo 'hello terminal'
$ echo -n is text here
.fi
.SH NOTES
Output is added only to the current pane's transcript and is not persisted across a page reload.
.SH SEE ALSO
clear(1), history(1)
